### 1. Test successful login (using the correct password)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "password": "123456"
}


### 2. Test failed login (using the wrong password)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "password": "wrong_password_test"
}


### 3. Test getting current status /auth/me
# Note: You need to run the "successful login" request first,
# copy the returned token, and replace the placeholder below.
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJyb2xlIjoiYWRtaW4iLCJpYXQiOjE3NzE4MTM4NjAsImV4cCI6MTc3MTgxNzQ2MH0.h0CJf-lvpA0V5vupaKohJM705IBGBLS1sfjJaqhC8NI


### 4. Test logout /auth/logout
# Similarly, replace the placeholder with your actual token.
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJyb2xlIjoiYWRtaW4iLCJpYXQiOjE3NzE4MTM4NjAsImV4cCI6MTc3MTgxNzQ2MH0.h0CJf-lvpA0V5vupaKohJM705IBGBLS1sfjJaqhC8NI


### 5. Test accessing a protected route without a token (Should return 401 Unauthorized)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/me